      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of living a performance instead of your true self is deeply painful and profoundly isolating. Please remember that the ease you see in others is often just an outward presentation, not the full reality of their internal experience. Your worth is not dependent on how easily you can seem to navigate life, and your struggle is valid even if it feels unseen. If the weight of this isolation becomes too much, please consider speaking with a therapist who can help you find ways to be authentically yourself.",
      "source": "target",
